MANIFESTATIONS
OF
CYSTIC
FIBROSIS
THE
DIAGNOSIS
OF
CYSTIC
FIBROSIS
IS
USUALLY
ESTABLISHED
BY
THE
PRESENCE
OF
CHRONIC
OBSTRUCTIVE
LUNG
DISEASE
ANDOR
GASTROINTESTINAL
COMPROMISE
TOGETHER
WITH
ELEVATED
SWEAT
ELECTROLYTES
OR
PATHOLOGIC
CHANGES
IN
TISSUE
BECAUSE
OF
ITS
HIGHLY
VARIABLE
GENETIC
PENETRANCE
THE
DISEASE
IS
CHARACTERIZED
BY
VARYING
DEGREES
OF
INVOLVEMENT
OF
DIFFERENT
EXOCRINE
SYSTEMS
